01:51.775 --> 01:58.366
And this is not any different for us, but the song that we're gonna be getting our time with is called The Joy of the Lord.

01:58.686 --> 02:03.534
And I'm reminded of Psalm 51 as we step into this song.

02:04.015 --> 02:08.482
Now Psalm 51 is written by a guy named David who you may be familiar with or not.

02:08.522 --> 02:10.565
This is the same David of David and Goliath.

02:11.026 --> 02:13.650
But this is a little later in his life after he's kind of

02:13.762 --> 02:15.805
messed up in a number of different ways.

02:16.266 --> 02:24.177
He actually fell in love with another woman's man's wife and then had that man killed so that he could take that woman as his own wife.

02:24.197 --> 02:26.300
So yeah, he kind of got a little sideways.

02:27.281 --> 02:35.372
But somebody came to him, confronted him about that bad choice and he came to God and said, I need forgiveness.

02:35.733 --> 02:37.375
And so God, would you please forgive me?

02:37.395 --> 02:39.378
And so this is what he says.

02:39.398 --> 02:42.162
We get to listen into his prayer to God.

02:42.402 --> 02:47.847
when he says, create in me a pure heart O God and renew a steadfast spirit within me.

02:47.867 --> 02:52.272
Do not cast me from your presence or take your Holy Spirit from me.

02:52.952 --> 03:00.360
And he says, restore to me the joy of your salvation and grant me a willing spirit to sustain me.

03:01.361 --> 03:07.406
So he asks for forgiveness and asks for the joy of the Lord to continue to come back into his life.

03:07.507 --> 03:11.090
And so that would sustain him and give him strength to move forward.

03:11.522 --> 03:13.024
but it's not just for him.

03:13.064 --> 03:14.806
And listen to what he says as he continues.

03:16.148 --> 03:39.858
So the joy that God gives to him restores to him is not only for him,

03:40.322 --> 03:43.506
but it's so that he can love and serve those around him.

03:44.106 --> 03:51.034
So today, as we sing this song, as we say that phrase, the joy of the Lord is my strength.

03:51.835 --> 03:57.322
I hope it's a reminder for you that the joy of the Lord is your strength today, but it's not just for you.

03:57.382 --> 04:06.112
That strength is so that you can love and serve your family, your friends, those around you towards the love of Christ.

04:06.372 --> 04:07.954
