18:53.696 --> 19:01.106
This has caused for tremendous celebration because it means that each of these individuals has opened up their hearts to the love and grace of Jesus.

19:01.767 --> 19:07.795
And each are declaring their desire to continue to be transformed by Him and to follow Him.

19:08.456 --> 19:13.042
So we thought it would be good and appropriate to pray over this group of people

19:13.218 --> 19:24.274
asking God to bless this time of sacrament and that this moment of public commitment would set a great trajectory of faith and followership long into the future.

19:24.875 --> 19:27.139
So let's join together and pray.

19:28.320 --> 19:39.377
Dear God, we thank you for the gift of sacrament and particularly the sacrament of baptism, which is a beautiful way for us to identify in both your suffering and your resurrection.

19:40.038 --> 19:42.962
It's a sacred moment of belonging and solidarity.

19:43.554 --> 19:47.981
And so Lord, we wanna just lift up each person who's getting baptized by their first name.

19:48.521 --> 20:04.285
We ask that you would be with Tracy and Jacob and Michelle, Ashlyn, Deborah, Brian, Louis, Lana, Shelley, Cameron, Savannah, Silas, Taylor, Samantha, Marcia, Larson, Mario, Abigail, and Kristen.

20:04.825 --> 20:09.412
And Lord, we just ask that you would hold each of these individuals in your hand.

20:10.133 --> 20:13.458
May this be the starting point of a journey of discovery

20:13.634 --> 20:17.360
and love, a journey of transformation and hope.

20:18.101 --> 20:21.766
May each of these individuals fall deeper and deeper in love with you.

20:22.387 --> 20:26.033
May they find comfort and purpose in your word.

20:26.654 --> 20:31.541
May they be daily reminded that you are raising them to a new life of grace.

20:32.423 --> 20:35.688
Sustain them, oh Lord, in your Holy Spirit.

20:35.708 --> 20:42.418
Give each of them the courage and the will to persevere through life's most difficult moments.

20:42.882 --> 20:45.645
Give them the passion to know and love you.

20:46.226 --> 20:52.813
Give each of them great joy and for them to continue to just be awestruck at your goodness and the strength of your mighty hand.

20:53.754 --> 20:56.917
Lord, I would also pray for us as a church, right?

20:56.937 --> 21:02.203
That Lord, you would help us surround each of these brothers and sisters with great support and love.

21:02.704 --> 21:07.529
May we only amplify the love and grace that they've already found in you.

21:07.549 --> 21:09.551
Guide and protect all of us.

21:09.831 --> 21:12.274
Oh Lord, we pray in your mighty name.

21:13.250 --> 21:31.704
I started to notice the problem one day when I walked outside and I saw my neighbor's new car.

21:31.724 --> 21:32.946
That was a real wake-up call for me.

21:45.794 --> 21:50.219
Who knew that inside that small box was the very thing I had been looking for this whole time?

21:50.239 --> 21:52.282
The illusion of having everything that I want.

21:53.844 --> 21:56.547
I used to ask my friends how their kids were so well behaved.

21:57.028 --> 21:59.551
Now my friends are coming to me with the same question.

22:00.532 --> 22:01.613
But I'll never tell.

22:04.697 --> 22:09.042
Why see life for what it is when you can see it through the life filter?

22:17.026 --> 22:19.871
Hey, Heritage, it is so great to be with you.

22:20.512 --> 22:24.900
I'm just excited about this opportunity I have and that we have to join this time together.

22:25.581 --> 22:26.923
Now, I have a question for you.

22:27.404 --> 22:32.193
When you travel, would you consider yourself a light packer, kind of a minimalist?

22:32.553 --> 22:37.181
Or would you consider yourself to be someone that basically takes everything, including the kitchen sink?

22:37.201 --> 22:39.525
Like, what would describe you?

22:40.427 --> 22:42.130
For instance, when you go camping,

22:42.306 --> 22:45.910
I don't know, maybe you love to go camping, maybe you loathe going camping.

22:46.331 --> 22:47.733
I'm personally not a camper.

22:48.474 --> 22:52.158
I don't know why anyone would want to pretend for four or five days that they're homeless.

22:52.498 --> 22:56.784
That just doesn't sound like a great time to me, but my wife and my girls love camping.

22:56.824 --> 22:58.846
And so because of that, I go camping.

22:59.367 --> 23:05.234
But when I go camping with my wife and with my girls, I'll just tell you, we don't want for anything.

23:05.442 --> 23:15.454
I'm sure my neighbors laugh hilariously when they watch us take 47 trips from our house out to the rented camper that we've rented for the weekend or for the week or whatever it is.

23:16.035 --> 23:20.200
And the great thing about it is that my wife cooks delicious food throughout the time.

23:20.260 --> 23:24.145
Camp food is just awesome from her, as is her normal food, I should say.

23:24.686 --> 23:28.991
But also, we never said to ourselves, oh, we left that at home.

23:29.312 --> 23:30.994
That never happens to us.

23:31.054 --> 23:32.095
It just doesn't happen.

23:33.056 --> 23:34.418
What about when you go on a trip?

23:34.818 --> 23:38.423
I'm wondering, do you know what one of these are?

23:38.464 --> 23:41.408
This is actually a luggage scale.

23:41.648 --> 23:42.810
Have you ever had to use one?

23:44.152 --> 23:50.301
I am not all that proud of this, but I have to tell you that I have to use one basically every time I go.

23:51.023 --> 23:54.989
Every single time I go on a trip, I'm basically pulling one of those out and using it.

23:55.489 --> 23:55.750
Why?

23:55.770 --> 23:56.711
I don't know.

23:56.731 --> 23:57.532
I just don't know.

23:57.592 --> 24:03.922
I guess I'm always kind of thinking that I want to plan for any contingency and anything that

24:04.034 --> 24:05.816
I just think I might need.

24:06.557 --> 24:09.040
I travel a fair amount.

24:09.741 --> 24:12.524
And whenever I travel, I always take a backpack with me.

24:12.805 --> 24:14.006
That's just kind of my deals.

24:14.206 --> 24:14.907
I take a backpack.

24:14.927 --> 24:18.111
Now, I want you to know, I haven't done anything special in this backpack.

24:18.131 --> 24:20.434
I haven't added anything that I don't normally travel with.

24:20.454 --> 24:26.581
So I just thought it'd be kind of fun for us to look at a normal backpack experience for Chris Conrad.

24:26.601 --> 24:28.283
Again, I didn't add anything to this.

24:28.303 --> 24:30.226
So this is my little computer bag.

24:30.246 --> 24:33.970
This is what my computers and my iPads and that kind of stuff are in.

24:34.178 --> 24:38.265
And then if you go to the next little pocket, here's my Bible.

24:38.706 --> 24:40.709
Here's a couple of books that I'm reading.

24:41.731 --> 24:46.639
Here's an old school notebook just in case I want to write anything down.

24:47.000 --> 24:50.045
Here's the stationery that I travel with with some stamps in it.

24:50.145 --> 24:51.527
I don't even know what this folder is for.

24:52.890 --> 24:53.511
So there we go.

24:53.651 --> 24:58.680
Oh, and then one of the things you're going to figure out is that I am into sound.

24:58.700 --> 25:00.082
Like I love good sound.

25:00.226 --> 25:06.916
So if I'm going to be gone for any period of time whatsoever, I'm taking a little tiny Bose speaker with me everywhere.

25:07.117 --> 25:07.798
That's just who I am.

25:08.158 --> 25:08.859
So there you go.

25:08.879 --> 25:10.021
And this little sucker is heavy.

25:10.422 --> 25:13.887
So, okay, that's, that's just two, that's just two pockets.

25:14.227 --> 25:15.209
I won't go through them all.

25:15.229 --> 25:15.990
I don't want to bore you.

25:16.511 --> 25:24.964
But here are every kind of computer cord or audio cord that I might use just in case I want to hook up my computer to a television.

25:25.845 --> 25:26.386
I've got,

25:26.562 --> 25:29.106
All kinds of, here's an HDMI cable.

25:29.447 --> 25:31.811
Here's something for a whole bunch of USB ports.

25:32.112 --> 25:35.838
Now again, I'm carrying this every, here's a portable mouse.

25:36.600 --> 25:40.146
I mentioned that I love, that I absolutely love like great sound, right?

25:40.206 --> 25:42.690
So here I'm going to get, yep, yep, right here.

25:42.811 --> 25:46.216
This is another set of bows, but this is in here.

25:46.337 --> 25:48.601
So they go on for when I run, all that kind of stuff.

25:48.621 --> 25:51.666
And honestly, I'll, I'll, I'll stop boring you now.

25:51.810 --> 25:53.432
but that just gives you a taste.

25:53.492 --> 25:57.397
And I've still got another probably 10 or 15 pounds with this stuff in there.

25:58.137 --> 26:01.962
Now, when we think about that kind of stuff, it can be a little funny at times.

26:01.982 --> 26:06.527
I mean, it's just like, okay, Chris, you need to learn how to be much more lean in yourself.

26:06.988 --> 26:07.829
And I probably do.

26:08.630 --> 26:16.519
It's one thing when we have to pay extra money for an extra weight on our bags or we have to make sure that we're under that 50 pound limit.

26:16.899 --> 26:19.282
That's one thing, but here's another question to ask.

26:19.970 --> 26:22.973
How much baggage are you carrying through life?

26:25.235 --> 26:32.081
How much baggage are you carrying as you walk through your daily routines in life?

26:32.962 --> 26:35.144
Because here's what I know and here's what I believe.

26:36.405 --> 26:40.569
I believe that many of us are carrying extra weight in our souls.

26:42.171 --> 26:46.315
Weight that the Heavenly Father does not intend for us to carry.

26:47.356 --> 26:49.778
Weight that is actually slowing us down

26:49.890 --> 26:54.296
and keeping us from all that the Father has for us.

26:54.316 --> 26:59.422
You know, we're in this series right now and we've been talking about families.

27:00.083 --> 27:08.494
And what I know and what I'm sure you know as well is that many of us are carrying weight from the family of origin that we come from.

27:09.555 --> 27:11.338
We picked up weight from that.

27:12.299 --> 27:17.906
And I just have to tell you, it is so incredibly easy to pick those things up.

27:18.658 --> 27:19.619
Let me give you an example.

27:20.099 --> 27:28.668
Do you remember when you were a kid and your parents, it could be your dad or your mom, either one, do you remember when they said something or did something?

27:29.148 --> 27:32.792
And in the back of your spirit, you said, I'm never gonna do that.

27:33.313 --> 27:35.375
Like when I get older, I'm never gonna do that.

27:36.316 --> 27:39.098
And then you grow up and you become an adult.

27:39.839 --> 27:41.200
And what do you find yourself doing?

27:42.201 --> 27:45.024
The very thing you said you'd never do.

27:46.105 --> 27:46.866
I'll never forget.

27:47.010 --> 27:50.976
growing up as a kid, my parents went to church a lot.

27:50.996 --> 27:55.822
And so because of that, they would, my mom was what they used to call the accompanist.

27:55.842 --> 27:58.967
She played the piano in this very large church that I grew up in.

27:59.427 --> 28:02.612
So we'd have to be at church at like 730 on a Sunday morning.

28:03.052 --> 28:12.185
And when it finally came after church was all over and we were heading home about 1230, my dad was gracious enough and he didn't want her to have to go home or him to have to go home and make anything for lunch.

28:12.205 --> 28:15.730
And so there's all that we'd always go out to eat after church on Sunday.

28:15.970 --> 28:17.612
But here was the weekly routine.

28:17.713 --> 28:18.975
I'm not making this up.

28:19.135 --> 28:24.002
This happened every week of my entire existing life growing up.

28:24.022 --> 28:29.410
We'd get in the car and my dad would look at my mom and he'd say, Miriam, where do you want to go to lunch?

28:30.132 --> 28:33.517
And my mom would look right back at him and say, Roy, I don't care.

28:33.557 --> 28:34.598
Where do you want to go?

28:35.780 --> 28:39.085
I don't care, Miriam, wherever you want to go, you've had a long morning.

28:39.726 --> 28:44.914
Roy, I don't, and they would go on and a fight would ensue every single time.

28:47.554 --> 28:48.115
Fast forward.

28:49.556 --> 28:50.217
I'm a pastor.

28:51.178 --> 28:52.679
My wife sings on the worship team.

28:53.460 --> 28:57.264
We had to get to church at 7.30 in the morning.

28:57.284 --> 28:59.747
We get in our little car after church was over.

29:01.048 --> 29:02.329
I would turn to my wife, Mary.

29:02.610 --> 29:04.391
Mary, where do you want to go for lunch?

29:05.553 --> 29:06.053
I don't care.

29:06.073 --> 29:08.436
Oh my gosh, it started again.

29:08.476 --> 29:11.999
Now that's kind of funny when you're talking about lunch plans.

29:13.060 --> 29:14.642
It's a whole other issue.

29:15.394 --> 29:19.559
when the things that you saw modeled in front of you were actually destructive in nature.

29:21.201 --> 29:31.312
And again, so many of us are carrying those around because many of us are living what I call an unexamined life.

29:33.034 --> 29:35.617
We've never kind of taken a time out.

29:36.057 --> 29:43.666
We've never taken a half time to kind of get aside, to kind of look at our lives from an outside perspective, if you will, almost out of having

29:43.746 --> 30:00.812
out of body experience, if you will, for just a moment, and look at our lives and ask ourselves the question, is the way that I'm living this life actually the most helpful way, the best way, the way that God has created me to live it?

30:00.832 --> 30:12.370
And what I want to encourage us to do for just a few brief moments today is to actually examine our life based on, based on our family of origins and the things that we picked up.

30:13.058 --> 30:20.245
Because if we're not proactive, we can end up passing on the things to the next generation that should not be passed on.

30:21.386 --> 30:24.790
Things that were passed on to us that we should not pass on to others.

30:25.250 --> 30:26.751
The Bible talks a lot about that.

30:27.692 --> 30:31.216
And many people have ended up calling it generational sin.

30:31.816 --> 30:34.379
Sin that just passes on from one generation to another.

30:35.420 --> 30:38.023
You know, there's a guy in the Old Testament by the name of David.

30:39.164 --> 30:41.586
And David in many ways was a great guy.

30:42.946 --> 30:46.369
But he had one flaw, at least.

30:47.631 --> 30:57.180
And that was that he couldn't keep his thought life in check and he couldn't keep his action life as it related to acting out with his thought life.

30:57.900 --> 31:00.443
So he ended up having an affair with a woman by the name of Bathsheba.

31:01.784 --> 31:07.470
And that one act had a disastrous impact on David's life.

31:07.970 --> 31:09.392
Now, God was still able to use him.

31:09.652 --> 31:10.352
God forgave him.

31:10.372 --> 31:11.033
There was mercy.

31:11.053 --> 31:11.954
There was grace.

31:12.098 --> 31:14.421
because David had a repentant heart, which was key.

31:16.945 --> 31:22.552
But that one act, man, it brought just all kinds of fury into David's life.

31:24.135 --> 31:26.918
Well, eventually David and this one Bathsheba had a son.

31:28.280 --> 31:29.081
His name was Solomon.

31:30.063 --> 31:31.024
And Solomon grows up.

31:32.406 --> 31:36.391
And Solomon follows in the exact same footsteps as his dad in this series.

31:36.412 --> 31:41.138
Matter of fact, if you will, let me read a little bit from First Kings,

31:41.250 --> 31:43.113
in the Old Testament, chapter 11.

31:44.334 --> 31:50.543
King Solomon loved many foreign women besides Pharaoh's daughter, who was his first wife.

31:51.885 --> 31:53.267
He talks about the women that he loved.

31:53.668 --> 32:05.044
Morbite women, Ammonite, Intermite, Sinianites, Hittites, they were from nations about which the Lord had told the Israelites, you must not intermarry with them because they will surely turn your heart after their gods.

32:05.926 --> 32:09.010
Nevertheless, Solomon held fast to them in love.

32:09.794 --> 32:11.697
He had, this is just crazy to me.

32:11.937 --> 32:16.424
He had 700 wives of royal birth and 300 concubines.

32:16.965 --> 32:19.689
And his wives and his wives led him astray.

32:20.210 --> 32:24.076
Can I just tell you, now I've been married to the same woman for almost 31 years.

32:24.497 --> 32:27.081
It takes everything I've got to try and make one woman happy.

32:27.161 --> 32:28.403
I can't imagine having 700.

32:28.704 --> 32:32.690
That's just out of my radar, absolutely.

32:32.710 --> 32:35.594
But here's the sad thing, as if there weren't enough sad things already.

32:36.716 --> 32:37.938
As Solomon grew old,

32:38.178 --> 32:40.441
his wives turned his heart after other gods.

32:41.001 --> 32:47.790
And his heart was not fully devoted to the Lord, his God, as the heart of his father, David had been before he had this affair with Bathsheba.

32:49.192 --> 32:54.178
He followed the goddess of the city-eyes and Molek, the detestable God of the Ammonites.

32:54.778 --> 32:56.981
So Solomon did evil in the eyes of the Lord.

32:57.201 --> 32:59.264
He did not follow the Lord completely.

32:59.684 --> 33:04.210
Now again, what happened there is that David had an issue in his life

33:04.482 --> 33:09.809
that he didn't get under control, and so he passed it on to his son Solomon.

33:11.491 --> 33:23.467
See, the sad thing about it is that many times if we live an unexamined life, we'll end up passing things on to our kids that God doesn't want passed on to them.

33:23.868 --> 33:29.235
There are some wonderful things about you that God would love to have passed on to your kids.

33:29.756 --> 33:31.698
But there are some other things he'd rather not.

33:31.718 --> 33:34.482
And what's sad about the David and Solomon story?

33:35.298 --> 33:47.456
is that because of Solomon's decision, it literally cost, and you can read it yourself, it literally cost millions of people either their lives or the destinies that God had for them.

33:48.418 --> 33:54.527
Because after Solomon was done being king, the entire nation of Israel was torn in two.

33:55.889 --> 34:00.616
And because of that, there are many people who ended up just forgetting God and going off their own way.

34:01.417 --> 34:04.722
And again, that generational sin that I talked about a few minutes ago just

34:05.346 --> 34:05.867
continued.

34:06.868 --> 34:10.554
If I can, let me just read you a couple of verses out of 2 Kings and 1 Kings.

34:11.135 --> 34:16.222
Jehoiakon did evil in the eyes of the Lord just as his father had done.

34:16.482 --> 34:17.744
His father and his father's footsteps.

34:18.586 --> 34:24.354
Ahaziah served and worshiped Baal and aroused the anger of the Lord, the God of Israel, just as his father had done.

34:25.296 --> 34:26.157
But you know the cool thing?

34:26.718 --> 34:28.280
The flip side of that was true as well.

34:28.300 --> 34:35.090
2 Kings 15, Azariah did what was right in the eyes of the Lord, just as his father

34:35.810 --> 34:36.791
Amazon had done.

34:38.013 --> 34:39.355
See, here's what's interesting.

34:39.555 --> 34:46.564
The most natural thing for us to do is to do what we saw modeled before us in front of us.

34:47.585 --> 34:53.372
Whatever our parents did, that's what, that's what becomes natural and normal for us.

34:53.933 --> 35:02.204
And that's why it's so important for us to examine our lives and the environment that we grew up in and ask ourselves, how has my life been impacted by that?

35:03.505 --> 35:04.146
And now,

35:04.994 --> 35:08.798
Now what is God's invitation to me based on what I grew up in?

35:10.680 --> 35:21.251
So I'm going to take that kind of mindset of, okay, what's true about me because of the home I grew up in and what is the Holy Spirit in inviting me to do as a result of that.

35:21.852 --> 35:29.140
I'm going to take that kind of thought and I'm just going to go through a couple of areas in my own upbringing and hopes that there'll be some meaning to it.

35:29.160 --> 35:30.221
I don't want this to be boring at all.

35:30.682 --> 35:34.866
I think it will be interesting and maybe even comical a little bit along the way.

35:35.202 --> 35:39.546
My mom and dad met when my dad was 23 and my mom was 14.

35:40.247 --> 35:45.492
My dad was in the Navy and he was based in San Diego and that's where my mom grew up in San Diego, California.

35:46.192 --> 35:47.473
And my dad came to an event.

35:47.954 --> 35:57.583
It was actually a Christian event called Youth for Christ and he just walked into this room and there was this young gal who looked older than she was playing the piano.

35:57.983 --> 36:01.106
And she was playing the piano for all the music that they were to do that night.

36:01.146 --> 36:04.309
And that young girl ended up being my mom.

36:04.329 --> 36:05.170
So that's how they met.

36:05.826 --> 36:11.393
My dad actually didn't find out how old my mom was until they went to get a wedding certificate.

36:12.133 --> 36:16.739
And my mom couldn't sign it because she wasn't 16 yet.

36:17.440 --> 36:18.060
True story.

36:18.881 --> 36:26.691
Now that probably clues you in to a little bit of my dad and who he was.

36:27.231 --> 36:32.978
My dad grew up in this, what I would call a very emotionally distant home.

36:33.090 --> 36:36.835
He had fine parents, but everybody in that home was just emotionally distant.

36:37.476 --> 36:43.885
My mom grew up in a very abusive home where she was abused in many different ways.

36:45.247 --> 36:54.840
And so you put these two people together, and I just have to tell you, they walked into their marriage with overweight baggage in their souls.

36:56.402 --> 37:01.970
Like, if their soul would have had some kind of scale, it would have been screaming.

37:02.114 --> 37:04.077
overweight, overweight, overweight.

37:05.099 --> 37:17.798
And given their background, ah, what they should have done as soon as they got married, if they got married, they should have come together and said, oh my goodness, we need to get someone, we need to go someone who's got some wisdom.

37:18.078 --> 37:22.805
We've got to figure out this marriage thing because they just fought.

37:22.825 --> 37:24.528
There was so much damage.

37:26.431 --> 37:31.218
Can I tell you what I think the Holy Spirit was inviting them to do?

37:31.490 --> 37:39.082
many, many, many, many years ago, I think he was inviting them to respond differently than they did.

37:39.924 --> 37:45.493
See, if our marriage struggles, the answer is not to give up, but to get wisdom.

37:47.295 --> 37:52.043
Every marriage is going to struggle every once in a while, and the answer is not to give up, but to get wisdom.

37:53.205 --> 37:58.834
That's why the message paraphrase talks about this in Proverbs 4 verse 7.

37:59.266 --> 38:01.790
Above all, and before all, do this.

38:02.250 --> 38:03.552
Get wisdom.

38:04.534 --> 38:06.096
Write this at the top of your list.

38:06.457 --> 38:07.719
Get understanding.

38:08.460 --> 38:12.165
In today's vernacular, I would say go see a great Christian counselor.

38:12.586 --> 38:18.935
Go see someone that can help you navigate the difficult conversations that you're trying to have, but you're not getting anywhere with.

38:19.917 --> 38:20.738
Please sit down.

38:20.758 --> 38:21.299
Can I tell you?

38:21.900 --> 38:29.010
My wife, Mary and I, we have sat down for probably throughout 31 years, almost a marriage, hundreds and hundreds of hours.

38:29.122 --> 38:33.248
of counseling just to make sure that our marriage could be all that it could be.

38:33.609 --> 38:35.512
And because of the stuff that we brought in.

38:36.573 --> 38:41.461
Now, I know what's happening right now is some of you men are thinking, I'm not going to go to counseling.

38:41.821 --> 38:42.042
Never.

38:42.202 --> 38:43.063
I'm not going to do that.

38:45.166 --> 38:47.330
Guys, can I ask you a question?

38:48.872 --> 38:55.602
Why would you watch a YouTube video on how to fish better,

38:56.098 --> 38:59.582
Why would you watch a YouTube video on how to fix your car?

39:01.184 --> 39:05.950
Last week, literally, I watched a YouTube video on how to fix my washing machine and it worked.

39:07.091 --> 39:08.053
Why would we do that?

39:08.113 --> 39:16.143
Why would we seek wisdom to fix a mechanical thing and we wouldn't seek wisdom to make our marriage everything that it can be?

39:17.925 --> 39:22.290
I wanna encourage you, please, let's have the humility

39:23.170 --> 39:28.976
to do what I think Holy Spirit was inviting my parents to do in that moment, which was seek wisdom.

39:29.417 --> 39:30.398
Get some help.

39:31.679 --> 39:35.744
It's not your fault, Roy, that you grew up in this emotionally distant home.

39:35.764 --> 39:39.868
It's not your fault, Miriam, that you grew up in this home that was very abusive.

39:39.888 --> 39:45.354
But now, if you're not careful, you're going to pass all that on to your kids unless you get some wisdom.

39:46.175 --> 39:46.636
So get it.

39:47.537 --> 39:50.720
And if your marriage is struggling, please don't sit there and just struggle and struggle.

39:51.181 --> 39:52.402
Get some help.

39:53.154 --> 39:56.958
go to someone who is gifted with discernment and gets some help.

39:57.158 --> 40:08.289
Number two, the second thing that I think that God was trying to teach my parents is that he uses our marriage partner to shape us into more of his image.

40:09.370 --> 40:10.491
Now, here's the thing.

40:10.651 --> 40:12.673
I think so many of us think that God wants us happy.

40:13.294 --> 40:13.874
And that's true.

40:13.914 --> 40:18.399
He is interested in our joy factor and to some degree our happiness factor.

40:18.939 --> 40:22.002
But I have to tell you, God is actually even more interested in our

40:22.402 --> 40:25.906
holiness in our ability to be more like him.

40:26.948 --> 40:28.630
And here's what's interesting.

40:28.650 --> 40:32.234
He uses our spouse to help bring that about.

40:33.035 --> 40:33.375
He does.

40:34.116 --> 40:40.044
If you're married, he'll use your spouse to help bring about the work that he wants to do in your life.

40:40.104 --> 40:45.170
Now, I just tell you, there are times when we just absolutely great against that.

40:45.931 --> 40:48.434
We say, ah, God, can you choose someone else?

40:49.218 --> 40:54.004
But the truth of the matter is that God wants to use those people that are so close to us.

40:54.945 --> 41:00.671
Because when He does that, the lessons go deeper and the change is greater.

41:02.153 --> 41:11.604
Ephesians chapter 5 verse 25 says, My responsibility is to love Mary.

41:12.565 --> 41:17.010
See, we all know that in school there's class time and then there's lab time.

41:17.346 --> 41:19.148
at least in non-COVID times, right?

41:19.168 --> 41:19.969
There's lab time.

41:20.430 --> 41:21.150
What can I just say?

41:21.671 --> 41:25.776
There's time in God's word that we need to spend in His word, but then there's the lab time.

41:26.056 --> 41:28.599
And our marriage is that lab time.

41:29.360 --> 41:32.804
It's that time when that is worked out in our lives.

41:33.124 --> 41:36.368
I have to say, in the home night group, my dad, he was an incredible servant.

41:36.608 --> 41:37.109
He really was.

41:37.449 --> 41:39.311
He served in a really wonderful way.

41:39.832 --> 41:41.214
Like he would help around the house.

41:41.274 --> 41:42.755
He very much helped.

41:42.775 --> 41:45.138
He did his, I mean, he cooked.

41:45.346 --> 41:46.467
a good amount.

41:46.607 --> 41:48.029
He would help my mom with the laundry.

41:48.069 --> 41:50.131
He would help with house cleaning and that kind of stuff.

41:50.151 --> 41:52.674
And he kept the outside of our home looking really, really nice.

41:52.714 --> 41:54.777
My dad was an incredibly hard worker.

41:54.837 --> 41:57.019
He grew up on a farm in Pennsylvania.

41:57.039 --> 41:58.401
And so he was a very hard worker.

41:58.901 --> 42:00.323
No problem in those areas at all.

42:00.643 --> 42:07.751
But my dad had some deep insecurities that he never dealt with.

42:07.771 --> 42:09.873
And he never allowed the Holy Spirit to change that.

42:10.894 --> 42:14.098
See, when he ran up against my mom in marriage,

42:14.434 --> 42:19.159
My mom, who is naturally stronger than him, caused him to become insecure.

42:20.500 --> 42:27.567
And instead of allowing the Holy Spirit to bring about security and to lay an incredible foundation in his life, he has never dealt with it.

42:28.348 --> 42:36.095
And because of that, he abdicated so much to my mom, and my mom ended up feeling isolated, isolated and alone.

42:37.577 --> 42:42.962
You know, Holy Spirit, I know, I just, I just know where my spirit, Holy Spirit was saying to my dad, Roy,

42:43.266 --> 42:46.531
Would you allow me to replace that insecurity with my confidence?

42:47.692 --> 42:54.482
Would you allow me to replace those times when you're fearful, you don't know what to do, with a sense of my direction?

42:55.203 --> 42:55.803
Would you do that?

42:56.444 --> 42:59.789
And I'm confident if my dad would have done that, Holy Spirit would have shown up.

43:00.430 --> 43:01.411
He absolutely would.

43:02.573 --> 43:04.456
Now, your issue may not be insecurity at all.

43:04.636 --> 43:05.357
It may be the opposite.

43:05.377 --> 43:07.279
You might be incredibly confident.

43:08.241 --> 43:11.986
But are you being tender enough towards those people in your home?

43:12.194 --> 43:21.248
Is Holy Spirit maybe inviting you to be a little bit more tender, to be a little bit more caring, to be a little bit more grace giving to the people in your home?

43:23.031 --> 43:26.456
Maybe the invitation to you from the Holy Spirit is, would you give up porn?

43:30.001 --> 43:34.648
Would you be willing to allow my power to help you in your area of anger management?

43:35.710 --> 43:38.354
Because when you get angry, everybody around you gets scared.

43:39.874 --> 43:45.080
Would you allow my Holy Spirit to work in the area of your addiction to alcohol or to drugs?

43:46.722 --> 43:55.451
Would you allow my Holy Spirit to come right to your place of need and let me fashion you into the person I originally created you to be?

43:56.673 --> 43:57.153
Would you do that?

43:57.233 --> 44:00.897
And that's an invitation from the Holy Spirit that's on the table.

44:02.319 --> 44:03.781
One last thing, very quickly.

44:04.982 --> 44:08.626
My parents, oh my goodness, they were

44:08.962 --> 44:10.244
horrible at money management.

44:10.925 --> 44:12.388
My mom was the CEO of a company.

44:12.408 --> 44:14.551
My dad was middle management and AT&T.

44:14.751 --> 44:15.993
They made plenty of money.

44:16.835 --> 44:20.080
But the problem is, once again, my dad advocated that responsibility to my mom.

44:20.360 --> 44:23.125
And my mom, oh my God, you know what she was trying to do?

44:23.305 --> 44:26.470
She was trying to heal her soul by spending more money.

44:28.333 --> 44:30.877
And as a result of that, their finances were a wreck.

44:32.340 --> 44:36.146
And coming out of that environment, I had to try and learn how to

44:36.418 --> 44:41.064
How to even think about money, because I love my parents to death, but they never taught me any of that.

44:42.045 --> 44:48.152
So the third thing that the Holy Spirit I think was trying to say to them is allow God's money principles to guide your life.

44:49.874 --> 44:52.037
Some of you have got that down, and I celebrate that.

44:52.337 --> 44:54.700
Others of you, God just encourage you.

44:56.122 --> 45:02.930
Exactly what Proverbs 21.5 says, the plans of the diligent lead to profit, as surely as haste leads to poverty.

45:04.578 --> 45:07.943
Have a financial plan, get into a Dave Ramsey class, do something.

45:09.204 --> 45:14.372
Okay, now, I've said everything I've said so far today to end with this.

45:16.094 --> 45:22.002
One of the most profound statements I've heard in the last two years came from a pastor in Nashville, Tennessee.

45:22.463 --> 45:23.644
Her name is Alex Seeley.

45:23.684 --> 45:26.368
She's an incredibly wonderful woman of God.

45:26.388 --> 45:33.458
And Alex said this, and I'll never forget it, whatever we don't allow the Holy Spirit to transform,

45:34.082 --> 45:35.063
we will transmit.

45:37.546 --> 45:47.157
Whatever we don't allow the Holy Spirit to transform, we will transmit to the next generation, which is exactly what Romans chapter 12 verse 2 says.

45:48.478 --> 45:49.980
Let God transform you.

45:50.341 --> 45:55.707
Let God transform you into a new person by changing the way you think.

45:56.367 --> 46:02.194
And then you will learn how to know God's will for you, which is good and pleasing and perfect.

46:03.682 --> 46:04.483
I could be wrong.

46:05.765 --> 46:16.938
But my guess is that the Holy Spirit has been speaking to you throughout this message about the baggage that you came into your adult life with because of the home that you grew up in.

46:18.080 --> 46:32.978
And he's been whispering into your spirit some things that he wants you to shed, some areas that he'd like to change, some areas he'd like to transform so that you don't transmit them anymore.

46:34.562 --> 46:37.766
Maybe it's time to see a Christian counselor and work some of those things through.

46:37.786 --> 46:39.228
I beg you to do that.

46:40.529 --> 46:50.081
Maybe it's time to take an honest look at some of the areas in your life that you know are negatively impacting the people that you love around you.

46:51.763 --> 47:03.538
Maybe Holy Spirit right now is inviting you and saying to you, you think that area in your life cannot change, but the truth of the matter is, is nothing is impossible with my power.

47:04.162 --> 47:06.826
That's what the Holy Spirit is saying to you.

47:06.846 --> 47:17.663
So I'm not above begging you to allow the Holy Spirit of God to bring into your spirit and your heart the transformation that he wants to bring.

47:17.683 --> 47:23.251
Would you take a few moments now and just think through that and invite Holy Spirit to bring change?

47:24.373 --> 47:33.106
And I promise you, if you'll actually look at the baggage and bring that before the Lord, he will transform it.

47:33.378 --> 47:35.321
because he has the power to do it.

47:35.341 --> 47:36.021
Would you pray with me?

47:38.785 --> 47:45.193
Holy Spirit of God, none of us are perfect except for you, Jesus.

47:46.495 --> 47:50.941
And because of that, none of us grew up in a perfect home.

47:52.363 --> 47:57.149
And because of that, all of us came out of our homes with some kind of baggage.

47:58.571 --> 48:01.074
And now as adults, we have a decision to make.

48:02.178 --> 48:12.027
Are we going to allow you to transform those areas in our life which may need a significant amount of effort to be transformed?

48:13.809 --> 48:17.412
Or are we going to transmit them to the next generation?

48:20.295 --> 48:26.341
God, regardless of the energy it's going to take to transform, you are a God who provides for all that.

48:26.922 --> 48:28.883
You're a God of limitless power.

48:29.304 --> 48:31.666
You can change us from the inside out.

48:32.290 --> 48:36.034
If that wasn't possible, then Romans 12 verse 2 wouldn't be there.

48:36.474 --> 48:45.403
There wouldn't be an invitation to allow you to transform us by the renewing of our minds so that we could experience all that you have for us.

48:46.764 --> 48:48.385
Your invitation is on the table.

48:49.967 --> 49:01.618
Holy Spirit, help us not to believe anything except for your power and your grace that is abundant for us to live into.

49:02.114 --> 49:21.282
And I pray that today would be the day for many people to walk away from their baggage, to walk away from the things that have been slowing them down, and to walk into all the freedom that you have from them as a transformed person by the power of your Holy Spirit working in our lives.

49:21.923 --> 49:29.274
For all that you do, we will give you praise in Jesus' name.

49:29.294 --> 49:29.394
Amen.

49:40.802 --> 49:43.024
I count on one thing.

49:44.325 --> 49:50.211
The same God never fails or will not fail me now.

49:50.812 --> 49:57.138
He won't fail me now in the waiting.

49:57.158 --> 49:59.860
The same God's never late.

50:00.261 --> 50:03.023
He's working all things out.

50:03.504 --> 50:06.747
He's working all things out.

50:07.348 --> 50:09.810
Oh, yes, I will.

50:10.210 --> 50:14.658
Yes, I will.

50:15.841 --> 50:19.668
That's your name.

50:20.169 --> 50:22.994
Oh, yes, I will.

50:23.014 --> 50:27.282
Sing for joy when my heart is heavy.

50:27.303 --> 50:30.108
Oh, my days.

50:30.128 --> 50:31.250
Oh, yes, I will.

50:46.370 --> 51:10.034
The same God who never fails will not fail me now He won't fail me now in the waiting The same God who's never late is working all things out He's working all things out

59:13.762 --> 59:17.167
She's so glad that you have a God that fights for you.

59:17.828 --> 59:31.708
So many times we can think of God as someone who kind of is absent or different or other than us, but to know that he is intimately involved in each battle and different things that are happening in our lives, hopefully is an encouragement for you today.

59:31.728 --> 59:41.682
And again, thank you for worshiping with us, for stepping into just this time of worship and the word and prayer as we have celebrated together.

59:42.178 --> 59:48.926
This has been such a great series about family and how we live in community with one another.

59:48.946 --> 59:54.193
We've heard story after story and people giving us feedback of how helpful it has been for them.

59:54.693 --> 59:59.599
And so if it has been impactful for you, we are so glad that God has been using it to speak to you.

59:59.960 --> 01:00:04.946
But you also want to let you know of a couple of other resources to help you further along in your journey.

